[Run the following command]
Sudo apt install jp2a imagemagick chafa

[Instructions]
-Create an images into acii converter with ansi escape code.
-Height and width auto calculation. (aspect ratio)
-Output to a seperate file.
-Add descriptions to the whole script for easier customization.
-You may use unicode characters as well. 
-Add an extensive help section.
-Chafa and jp2a are to have the blocks preset and the others are just for chafa. (make the --random-all command know that)

[Features]
#   â€¢ Global randomization (--random-all) with full preview
